as long as i’m on this topic, note the limit on debit card interchange (affecting only large banks, which charge commanding portion of all overdraft fees for various reasons) was a) designed to rap banks on the knuckles for financial crisis and b) encourages overdraft fees.

i have done this by accident a few times, with the logical chain being “since loans aren’t designed to accelerate you on average are paying interest on half the initial principal, and in lieu of doing calculus or an amortization table can now just multiply trivially.” https://t.co/yayrkwmnmu
@infornomics february valuations for u.s. bank stocks were systemically overvalued for exactly this reason. i take no particular position on whether we’ve successfully priced it in since then.

attending microconf today for the first time in a few years. i typically cover a lot of the talks at a high rate of tweets; if you’re less interested in bootstrapped saas/etc businesses then you may want to mute me for the next 48 hours or so.
